 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Production Artist - Part-Time | Work-at-Home Southern Graphic Systems, LLC 106 reviews United States Remote Part-time Southern Graphic Systems, LLC 106 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Part-time Full Job Description About SGS 
SGS is a global leader in integrated packaging and marketing production for some of the largest consumer brands, retailers, pharmaceutical companies and printing/converting industries in North America, Europe, and Latin America. 
 
 Join the Team 
We’re looking for members to join our Production Art team in a work from home arrangement. 
If you’re looking for a part-time, flexible “gig” that lets you work on multiple projects for some of the world’s largest brands, this could be the role for you. Set your own schedule, forget about commute time and wear what you want to work – because your home is your office! The position provides the opportunity to work up to 30 hours/ week with 40 hours of sick time and competitive wages in lieu of benefits. 
To be eligible, candidates must be able to provide their own equipment and meet specific system and network requirements. 
About the Job 
You’ll help execute packaging artwork for some of the largest Consumer Packaged Goods brands in the world. 
Your impact and contribution 
Ensure job instructions are aligned to artwork 
Manipulate files to match customer specs 
Verify colors used and file resolution 
Receive product definitions from sales, project managers or production managers 
Adjust art to meet print requirements 
Assign color builds and Pantone ink swatches to art elements 
Check job to ensure accuracy of copy, content, color designations, and job data / labels 
Ensuring accuracy of final data deliverable such as, PDF, AI, and EPS 
Complete all required checklist(s) in full, with any errors found subsequently corrected 
Flag errors or deviations from standard work procedures 
What You’ll Need 
macOS 10.14 (Mojave) and newer  or  Windows 10 (or Server 2012 R2) and newer 
Dual Monitor Set-up 
Broadband or LTE Data that tests under 45ms latency when loaded (lower latency is better) 
15 Mbit down / 3 Mbit up is minimum (higher bandwidth is better) 
Test network requirements at https://speedof.me using an ethernet cable if possible 
Educational & Experience Minimum Requirements
 At least one year of production art experience with knowledge of CPG industry preferred 
Proficient in Adobe Creative Suite 
Strong typographic and layout skills, attention to detail, and outstanding organization 
Good understanding of digital file formats (pdf, tiff, eps) for Mac and PC’s 
Proofreading skills required 
Competency Requirements 
Ability to pick-up worked art files performing alteration amends following work order instructions (examples of these artwork manipulations will involve text/copy changes, repositioning, placement and/or removal of graphic elements) 
Ability to work independently 
Ability to QC work and ensure the accuracy of own files 
Strong interpersonal, communications and relationship skills 
Highly organized, deadline-driven, self-starter, and high level of attention to detail 
Ability to read, understand and follow work instructions, specifications, workflow diagrams and SOPs 
Equal Opportunity Employer/Protected Veterans/Individuals with Disabilities 
